Real-Time System

TrustBridge supports real-time events using Socket.IO.

Frontend clients can connect and join their user room:

import { io } from "socket.io-client";

const socket = io(API_URL);

socket.emit("join", user.id);

Supported events:

notification:new
support:message
API Authentication

JWT protected routes require:

Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN

API-key protected routes require:

x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY
Main API Endpoints
Auth
POST /api/auth/register
POST /api/auth/login
POST /api/auth/verify-email
POST /api/auth/resend-verification
GET  /api/auth/me
Vendors
POST   /api/vendors
GET    /api/vendors
GET    /api/vendors/top-rated
GET    /api/vendors/search?query=tech
GET    /api/vendors/me
PATCH  /api/vendors/me
GET    /api/vendors/:id
PATCH  /api/vendors/:id
DELETE /api/vendors/:id
GET    /api/vendors/:id/trust-score
Reviews
POST   /api/reviews
GET    /api/reviews/vendor/:vendorId
PATCH  /api/reviews/:id
DELETE /api/reviews/:id
Reports
POST   /api/reports
GET    /api/reports
GET    /api/reports/:id
PATCH  /api/reports/:id/status
DELETE /api/reports/:id
Transactions
POST  /api/transactions
GET   /api/transactions/vendor/:vendorId
GET   /api/transactions/:id
PATCH /api/transactions/:id/status
Disputes
POST   /api/disputes
GET    /api/disputes
GET    /api/disputes/:id
PATCH  /api/disputes/:id/status
DELETE /api/disputes/:id
Documents
POST   /api/documents/upload
GET    /api/documents/vendor/:vendorId
PATCH  /api/documents/:id/verify
DELETE /api/documents/:id
Support Tickets
POST  /api/support/tickets
GET   /api/support/tickets/my
GET   /api/support/tickets
PATCH /api/support/tickets/:id/status
POST  /api/support/tickets/:id/messages
Notifications
POST   /api/notifications
GET    /api/notifications
PATCH  /api/notifications/:id/read
PATCH  /api/notifications/read-all
DELETE /api/notifications/:id
Developer/API Keys
POST   /api/developers/api-keys
GET    /api/developers/api-keys
DELETE /api/developers/api-keys/:id
